### JPQL (Java Persistence Query Language)

JPQL is an object-oriented query language similar to SQL but operates on JPA entities rather than database tables.

### @Query with JPQL

```java
@Query("SELECT u FROM User u WHERE u.email = :email")
Optional<User> findByEmail(@Param("email") String email);

@Query("SELECT u FROM User u WHERE u.age BETWEEN :min AND :max")
List<User> findByAgeRange(@Param("min") int min, @Param("max") int max);
```

### Named Queries

```java
@Entity
@NamedQuery(name = "User.findByEmail",
    query = "SELECT u FROM User u WHERE u.email = :email")
public class User { ... }

// Repository
@Query(name = "User.findByEmail")
Optional<User> findByEmail(@Param("email") String email);
```

### Native Queries

Use `nativeQuery = true` for database-specific SQL.

```java
@Query(value = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE MATCH(name) AGAINST(:keyword IN BOOLEAN MODE)",
       nativeQuery = true)
List<User> fullTextSearch(@Param("keyword") String keyword);
```

### Aggregate Queries

```java
@Query("SELECT COUNT(u) FROM User u WHERE u.active = true")
long countActiveUsers();

@Query("SELECT NEW com.example.dto.OrderSummary(o.customer, SUM(o.total)) " +
       "FROM Order o GROUP BY o.customer")
List<OrderSummary> getOrderSummaries();
```

### Subqueries

```java
@Query("SELECT u FROM User u WHERE u.id IN " +
       "(SELECT o.user.id FROM Order o WHERE o.total > :minTotal)")
List<User> findUsersWithHighValueOrders(@Param("minTotal") BigDecimal minTotal);
```

codeExample:
@Repository
public interface EmployeeRepository extends JpaRepository<Employee, Long> {

    @Query("SELECT e FROM Employee e WHERE e.department.name = :deptName " +
           "ORDER BY e.salary DESC")
    List<Employee> findByDepartmentOrderedBySalary(@Param("deptName") String deptName);

    @Query(value = "SELECT * FROM employees WHERE YEAR(hire_date) = :year",
           nativeQuery = true)
    List<Employee> findByHireYear(@Param("year") int year);

    @Query("SELECT AVG(e.salary) FROM Employee e WHERE e.department.id = :deptId")
    Double averageSalaryByDepartment(@Param("deptId") Long deptId);
}
